    "text": "<@UDQKHNP51> The best resource for someone who doesn’t (yet) know category theory is the free book “Seven sketches in compositionality” by Fong &amp; Spivak. Several chapters explore uses of wiring diagrams. But be warned, this is a (introductory) mathematics textbook, so don’t expect it to be light reading.",
